        "creatureType": "",
        "details": {
            "description": "<p>An overwhelming feeling of being watched wells up in the minds of those in the room, an instant before an eerie red eye opens in the western wall.</p>",
            "disable": "<p><span data-pf2-check=\"deception\" data-pf2-dc=\"22\" data-pf2-traits=\"haunt\" data-pf2-label=\"Appear Uninteresting DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Deception</span> (trained) to appear uninteresting to the watching eye (and thus be ignored by it) or <span data-pf2-check=\"religion\" data-pf2-dc=\"22\" data-pf2-traits=\"haunt\" data-pf2-label=\"Ward Against Being Seen DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Religion</span> (trained) to ward against being seen by or affected by the eye.</p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 4
            },
            "reset": "<p>The haunt becomes inert at the end of any round in which there are no frightened creatures it can see. It stays dormant for 1 hour, after which point it resets.</p>",
            "routine": "<p>(1 action) The eye glances about, and those it can see (whether in area <strong>C4</strong> or outside of it) take [[/r 4d6 #mental]]{4d6 mental damage} (<span data-pf2-check=\"will\" data-pf2-dc=\"21\" data-pf2-traits=\"haunt\" data-pf2-label=\"Watching Wall DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Will</span> save) as fears of being watched impart ripples of pain.</p>\n<p>A creature that takes mental damage from this effect doesn't reduce their frightened value at the end of their next turn</p>"
        },
