                "description": {
                    "value": "<p data-visibility=\"gm\"><strong>Trigger</strong> A living creature remains in area <strong>C4</strong> for at least 1 round;</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> An overwhelming wave of paranoia fills area <strong>C4</strong>. Each creature in the room must attempt a <span data-pf2-check=\"will\" data-pf2-dc=\"25\" data-pf2-traits=\"emotion,enchantment,fear,mental\" data-pf2-label=\"Someone is Watching DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Will</span> save, with the following results. An eerie red eye then opens in the center of the western wall, looking about the room, and the haunt rolls initiative.</p>\n<div data-visibility=\"gm\"><hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Frightened]{Frightened 1} and feels like someone or something is watching them for as long as they remain frightened.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Frightened]{Frightened 2} and treats no one as an ally as long as they remain frightened.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Frightened]{Frightened 3} and is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Confused]{Confused} as long as they remain frightened.</p>\n</div>"
